    "language": "english",
    "review": "I want to like this game... I really do. I just.... don't like it.\nMoving is extremely slow, be it serving or swimming, it just feels bad all the time. Even when you get upgrades, it sucks.\nThere's a restaurant side of things, which I genuinely preferred over the diving, which is pretty bad in a game about diving. And quite frankly, that preference is minimal, the restaurant was \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 too.\n\nThe characters are extremely clich\u00e9. Fat lazy guy who doesn't want to do anything but inevitably has to. Fat computer dork who loves anime characters and will force you to fight giant squids to get his toys. Greedy capitalist who opens a shop just for you even though you're his prime source of profit and survivability. Samurai sushi guy who is cringy on levels never seen before. And finally a cat that you cannot pet. You can feed the cat, but finding cat food is obscenely rare. Good luck getting the achievement to feed the cat 20 times, it's rare as hell for a reason.\n\nThe underwater part of the game consists of diving for resources, doing QTE's and watching your oxygen. If you run out, it doesn't reload to an earlier save, you waste that day coming back with only one thing... I alt F4'd and reloaded a save, because... well obviously. I have staff to pay, if I come home empty handed, that's going to suck.\n\nThe game is riddled with attempts at humour, maybe you'll find it funny. I didn't... From Cringy attempts at climate activists to Pok\u00e9mon cards that don't actually net you anything, you collect them for the sake of collecting.\n\nThe dialogue is unskippable and also unvoiced(Except for a few random noises every time someone talks, often repeated... very often... extremely often.). You can just click through it, but there's no skip all button. Which would be nice, or a \"no dialogue\" option, which would be godly. Because this game wastes your time, lots of your time. Every time you get a quest or anything like that, expect to have to skip past Dave whining. Again... He whines more than I do in this review.\n\nIt tries to turn everything into an annoying minigame. Like when you get a blowtorch to get to a boss fight, you have to keep it in a circle while it very very slowly creeps along a line. It's not exciting, it's not hard, it's just boring.\n\nThen there's the predators. You get a lot of guns in this game, for the start of the game, they all suck. Sleeping dart finally work on a fish? Turns out it's too big to fit in your pack and you need to kill it, oh, that woke it up.... So what was the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 point? Because just harpooning it would've done the job just fine. There's sharks that are far easier to catch if you have guns. They have annoying QTEs that sometimes bug out. They also take down your oxygen, which also serves as your health bar. \n\nFinally, you catch these fish to sell in your restaurant. Which is quite simply one of the worst implemented mechanics I've ever seen.\nPut something on your menu and change your mind? You have to delete it... you don't get to pick something else for the menu, no, you caught all that fish and wasted your time doing it. So if you put something on the menu by mistake, tough \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665. Alt F4 to start over I guess. This is before even opening the restaurant. Also if you take food to someone and they leave, yeah, that food is gone. Get better staff I guess.\n\nTL:DR Ultimately, my biggest issues with this game are both the story and the dialogue. I'd overlook the lack of likeability in any of the characters If not for the fact that the game is hellbent on forcing me to speak to them every 20 seconds. I just want them to shut the hell up and let me play the damn game.\nBut then there is the damn game. Riddled with minigames, catching fish feels very slow, movement feels sluggish. Maybe I don't want to just play the damn game either. I'd refund it if I could, but it took me a while to realise that the game wasn't getting any better. It started off \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, it continued to be \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665. I wanted to like it... I really don't.\n\nThank you for reading, or skipping the review entirely. Either way, have a lovely day, even if you disagree with me.",
