    "language": "english",
    "review": "100%'d the game so this is a negative review from a big fan, only for the Jungle DLC. (I will change it to positive after a month tho, still love the game.)\n\nWhat attracted me the most in the base game was the atmosphere of the deep sea, exploring new fish and strong message of ocean conservation. However in Jungle DLC they just [spoiler] blew up an ancient whale in half, no explanation or remorse from the characters. [/spoiler]\n\nI get that it's just fictional, I also like edgy, satirical humor, but this one doesn't land. [spoiler] The whale wasn't a villain, it didn't deserve to die, [/spoiler] feels weird and inconsistent with the base game's tone.\n\nThe story line was underdeveloped and they put a lot of effort in adding many different mechanics inspired by other games. Can be fun but forcing them into the main story is frustrating for those who don't enjoy, say, turn base RPGs, fighting games, rhythm games, sims, etc. \n\nAnd for those who do enjoy the genre, better off just play those games directly than a cheaper version in a fish catching game. (Also the music game part in Jungle DLC was bad for even music game enjoyer, way too long and unclear beats. The farming part was also tedious, why do you have to shake a tree three times to get three fruits? Even ACNH doesn't do that.)\n\nI understand it's been years and the developers may have new visions. I still love Dave but it's going into a direction that doesn't resonate with me anymore.",
