    "review": "i must have been living under a rock, because i only heard about this game recently on twitter when i saw that dave was getting a skin in fortnite. i thought that he looked so sweet, so i checked out this game on steam. i was a little unsure about the trailer because i get kind of nervous with unfamiliar mechanics and i\u2019m pretty achievement-driven in my games lol, but the reviews seemed really positive.\n\ni am SO glad i purchased this game and took the plunge and bought all the dlc. the gameplay is sooo, so relaxing. the boss fights aren't too easy, but definitely not hard either; the perfect in-between. each day in-game, i can't wait to work in the sushi bar. i get excited when i catch new fish and love the challenge of catching them all in the best quality, the characters are real and charming, the colours are beautiful, the minigames are fun, and more. i've already sunk in nearly 50 hours, and i am so excited to sink in even more!\n",
