    "language": "english",
    "review": "[h2]Introduction:[/h2]\nThis is a spectacular game that never runs out of things to impress you with. It is essentially a fishing game that combines the aspects of an array of different genres into one cumulative gaming experience. It allows you to run your own artisanal sushi restaurant, start a flourishing farm, and catch a variety of fauna and flora in a nearby ocean hole. Though this is just the tip of the iceberg; there is a lot more positive stuff this game does well at. \n\n[h2]Eclectic, cinematic cutscenes:[/h2]\n\nThis game does an amazing job at creating cutscenes that keep you glued to the screen. Every once in a while, the game will throw in an amusing cutscene that will, I guarantee\u200c you, have you laughing. However, the game manages to incorporate cutscenes without making them feel oversaturated or repetitive. There is diversity. Occasionally, there could be a mellow, serene music interlude. A few moments later, a fraught, tense enemy introduction cutscene might play. Also, the game establishes characters through these cutscenes. These moments help you understand a characters overall disposition and feeling they exude, all through well-crafted animations and visuals. I would even go as far as saying that this game is known for their humorous cutscenes that help move the story forward.\n\n[h2]Freedom to move at your own pace:[/h2]\n\nOne thing I love about this game is how much liberty you have. You are not restricted to one play style. This might come up as a surprise, but with how the game encourages personal freedom, you do not even have to fish near the mid-game if you do not want to. Rather, you can continue farming plants and vegetables or continue progressing with the story line. Other than occasional D-days\u2014situations in which you need to complete a task within a specific time\u2014the game is really laidback. There may be a few rough moments at the start where you do *ahem* die, but you always learn from your mistakes and improve no matter what.\n\n[h2]An enjoyable, addictive, yet simple gameplay loop:[/h2]\n\nThis game creates a gameplay loop that is extremely satisfying yet very straightforward. It keeps everything simple without complicating too many features. This allows you to spend time continuing with the game rather than spending hours learning one convoluting game addition. I will not delve too deep into what the gameplay revolves around, but it can boil down to this: Catch fish in an enigmatic underwater hole, then turn your daily catch into sushi to expand your artisanal sushi restaurant. Of course, the game throws a few addition features occasionally to spice things up, such as farming or mining, but everything revolves around fishing and your sushi restaurant.\n\n[h2]The constant introduction of novel gameplay experiences:[/h2]\n\nThis game is packed with extensive content that never leaves you without anything to do. I do not want to spoil too much of the game, but here is what you can expect to be encountering in your play through: Unique boss fights, eccentric customers, cook offs, stealth missions, and different ways of procuring ingredients. Know that you will never feel bored; there will always be new achievements to strive for, quests to finish, or ways to progress through the main storyline. This makes every moment feel fresh and novel.\n\n[h2]Conclusion:[/h2]\nOverall, this is an extremely well-rounded and satisfying game that I think deserves many future DLC's and updates. It incorporates many unique features into one gaming experience, ensuring that you will never get bored. The cutscenes in the game are extremely well animated and help build the perfect mood for particular moments. If you want a game that you will find yourself playing for a copious amount of time, buy Dave The Diver. It will not disappoint you.",
