    "language": "english",
    "review": "Dave the diver is one of those games that you love, even with the simplicity this ame offers, guidance talmos any problem you migh have throughout the walkhrough. Easy puzzles, easy missions, also very straightfortward, allthatacompanied by variety of fish species, locations under and above waterline, characters with different personalities, funny dialogues with some inside jokes, really nice artstyle and lets not forget 4 great DLC\u00b4s, 2 of which are completely for free! I know that the 2 which are free arent as content-rich as the latest jungle DLC release or Ichibans holiday, but whats free counts nevertheless. I must say that this game has brought me some great satisfaction, I have spent 35 hours only on base game, 2 hrs on dredge, 2 on ichibans, 0,5 on godzilla and around 9-10 hours on the new jungle DLC, I was never bored.\n\nLets breakdown each and every DLC:\nDredge: Amazing content, loved the events, newly added species and challenges. 5/5.\n\nIchibans holiday: Funny DLC, loved the characters, loved dismantling the pirate base, somewhat innovative or just unusual gameplay (top-down duels in the base) also the food and drink challenges added an already typical (typical for this game universe and mintrocket) layer of gameplay. 4/5.\n\nGodzilla: Short, almost like just an event DLC, still nice to get for free. 4/5.\n\nJungle: I must declare, that this DLC aint the same as the base game, ther is lots of different approach in terms of minigames and side missions, also there is additional crafting of new equipment and tools.I kinda loved the different game styles that are put into this game, especially the forrest \u201eminigame\u201c is a nice addition. What I would criticise in this DLC is that sometimes the puzzles are just like brainless and also you can mostly expect the same to happen in similar situations throughout the game (for example the \"miniboss\" encounters in some side missions). Last thing I wold like tt adress is that this game lets you upgrade only your diving suit, oxygen tank and harpoon from the original set of equipment, and  dyou can upgrade them only once each, which is not so entertaining, with that said I believe that they (studio) didn\u00b4t have any better option with how the story is led. To conclude, it is an amazing DLC and I personally loved most of the stuff in this extra content <3. 5/5.\n\nTo conclude, the main game is undoubtly 5/5, the DLCs sit around 4/5, but I recommend you to try them all. The game is well worth the full price. Thank you for your attention.",
