    "review": "tldr; buy it, but beware of a few things\r\n\r\nI like this game a lot. Amazing charm and super fun. The animations of this game matched with a consistent whimsey throughout shows how much love is in this game. I really enjoy the boss battles and their designs. Anything with a focus on fish and collecting them will always put me in a choke hold.  \r\n\r\nHOWEVER, this game clearly is for an older audience but on so many occasions it holds your hands through puzzles that are so obvious. And then at other times you're confused by ui and what anything means. Does \"send fish to fish tank\" mean all my fish? Does \"re dispatch\" collect what my employees have procured or does it send them out again without collecting. There was a quest that mentioned you needed to go to a shipwreck so I obviously go to the shipwreck that we had a plot event at but no it's some random location that also is a shipwreck? With no map it's just a bit annoying to have this vague phrasing. There is no difficulty in puzzle gameplay but consistent difficulty with poor phrasing or unclear ui. \r\n\r\nFishing in this game takes a lot of time. You will spend 90% of your game fishing and to be honest there is a little bit of dread every time I go into the ocean. This is because failure is very punishing. If you spend 30 mins collecting and fighting fish, and maybe are in a bad location so you can not get to an air tank or a quick snipe from an aggro fish, and you end up dying. You lose everything, besides one item you can choose. This has happened to me maybe 2-4 times maybe? It always makes me bad. It feels like I've wasted my time because it is such a time sink every time you go fishing. \r\n\r\nI don't know, I want to love this game but I do find myself groaning or gritting my teeth to try and get through everything because it feels like busy work a lot of the times.",
