    "author_last_played": 1782438473,
    "language": "english",
    "review": "Can't decide what you want to play next? That's alright, Dave's got you covered. From the first step into the water Dave the Diver appears to be more than a diving simulator. It can't decide what it wants to be, and that's the best part of Dave. You manage the restaurant (time-management/business), collect fish through various methods (netting, harpoons, tranq guns and firearms), and play diverse mini-games that are multi-genre in nature. If you like unpredictability, and entertaining side games that meaningfully apply to your in-game goals, play Dave. Period. No questions asked. It's a masterpiece like no other. The cutscenes are funny, characters are memorable, and the storyline feels engaging. It pulls on your heart strings, and brings a perfect blend of intentional game direction and freedom of play. If you haven't played Dave the Diver, I recommend you do so.",
