    "review": "After a few long hours, I came to the conclusion that the game is not about diving, almost not at all. \n\nWe got a lot of cutscenes, a tutorial after a tutorial and a lot of pop-ups to click through. Ultimately, we spend most of the time skipping conversations with clich\u00e9 and even\u2026 cringe NPCs. The graphics look nice on the first glance, but after a while, shortcomings are surfacing - it\u2019s a mashup of different assets, some of which are not pixel art. Random shaders and particle bugs become visible after the first location. I liked a variety of different animations tho.\n\nOverall, it\u2019s not such a bad game, but it's definitely underdeveloped and advertised in the wrong way. It\u2019s not as good and polished as the Dredge, it lacks a \u201cnice element\u201d from the Stardew Valley and other cozy games. Diving itself is fun, but it's hardly enough to keep up with everything else.",
