    "language": "english",
    "review": "This game suffers ADHD. The core gameplay is weak and to hide that problem, it's riddled with so many irrelevant half-cooked mini games. If you are suffering from ADHD and looking to maximise your suffering, this is the game for you.\n\nFor the first 2-3 hours, it will hook you in with the core game play (fishing and managing restaurant), so that you won't be able to refund the game. However, after that, the game stops being a fishing game but turns into a fetch play where you are mostly spending time running errands for people and doing mini games (race game, card game, farming of many different types at different locations, rhythm game, hide and seek, etc), that are not even related to the main play loop. They just wanted to have people play for a LONG period of time, and I guess it's probably because it looks good in their books for their investors? But honestly, it's such a drag and the entire game can be reduced down to 3-4 hours in total. Such a waste of time.",
