    "author_last_played": 1782730936,
    "language": "english",
    "review": "Overall its a good game but some of the character design and a few of the boss fight can be really fustrating. I know its by design, like we are suppose to hate them, be imagine some of the worst people you have work with and having to see them in this game. It probably won't happen but taking out that lying egotisic fish guy and hopefully getting rid of the Watson guy who is just annoying to fight will make this game a 10/10, so for me its a 8/10 right now.\r\n\r\nIn this game you hunt fish, have a limit capacity to carry and a limit air capacity (which also serves as the hp bar), there are random crates which can give items, weapon, weapon upgrade, O2 and ingrident lying around. Some fishes (espically sharks) are hostile, some are really rare. They can be caught, either sold as sushi or use to upgrade your sushi. If you catch them alive, There is a chance to get an egg which can be rasied at the fish farm, get 2 of them and they will reproduce. There is also regular farming and interacting with fish people for trades, mini-games, daily quests, etc.\r\n\r\nA side note, there are limited time DLC, which can annoy people since we still haven't gotten all the DLC, which versions like the switch has, like guilty gear. So maybe focus on that first?\r\n\r\nMinor spoiler alert:\r\nSo far in this game, only 3 death. First is from an inexpirence encounter with the whitetip shark, so just rookie mistake, once you get the hang of things, this fight is a cakewalk. The second is my first encounter with the shark boss (forget his name, you enter at night through the vortex), he will shred you. Last one is from the Watson guy, for the second fight, you need to dodge most of the time, which can be annoying since he loves charging at you and there is only one way to damage him and that comes from bouncing one of his own attack back at him. This is after doing a while mini quest, which is fustrating since if you failed, start over.",
