    "language": "english",
    "review": "what a fun rogue lite.  funny, entertaining, light hearted, Dave's character building is subtle but genuinely affectionate.  the subtle anime silliness in that undertale like graphics and yet the underwater still looks like totally amazing and the ocean life is realistic in looks and movements.  this game has a personality that tugs me in so many ways, but i guess the chill vibes around a caribbean feel, sushi , relaxing diving in the waters, oh my god... like i can't believe how much i like this game.   and yet i know it is completely unrepeatable and would only be gimicky at best reskinned in any other fashion.  I am as I just checked, 30 hours into playing this game and there is still new expansive content happening and i bought no expansions btw.  there is just more and more going on , side stories, unique characters, new quests, farming, collecting, pictures, and it just keeps going, never would have imagined so much packed into this 10 dollar game i got when it was on sale of course.  worth double that.",
