    "author_last_played": 1782767245,
    "language": "english",
    "review": "Dave the Diver is widely celebrated as a standout indie title that blends deep-sea exploration with sushi restaurant management.\r\nAfter watching **CohhCarnage stream the game, I decided to purchase it and found it to be an incredibly rewarding experience that far exceeded the simple premise of diving and fishing.\r\n\r\nThe game is a great game because it constantly introduces new mechanics and mini-games that keep the gameplay loop fresh and engaging.\r\nBeyond the core loop, I encounter a vast array of fun stuff, including seahorse racing, aquatic photography, gambling in a merfolk casino, and various rhythm-based concert mini-games.\r\nThis relentless stream of variety ensures that the 30/ 60(100%)-hour adventure never grows stale, offering something for every type of player. \r\n\r\nI and many others praise the game for its charming characters, heartfelt story, and beautiful pixel art.  The developers successfully meld seemingly disparate systems, like RPG combat, time management, and exploration into a cohesive and addictive whole.\r\nIt is a delightful surprise that offers more content and depth than one might expect from a retro-style indie RPG.\r\n\r\nNow its Time for the Jungle :D",
