    "language": "english",
    "review": "Dave the diver, after finishing it, has me with mixed feelings about the game. \n\nLet me start by saying that the game has a tonne of charm, humour and is clearly a labour of love by the devs + the crossovers/dlc are so well implemented (I'm looking at you, Streets of Rage and Balatro). \n\nThe gameplay loop is also satisfying - dive into water, get fish, open sushi bar and serve said fish, rinse and repeat whilst improving along the way with farms, workers + automation, etc and the story is also a nice little mystery to be solved as well coupled with smaller side stories which complemented the main story.\n\nThe soundtrack is great, the minigames are fun and the puzzles + bosses whilst on the lighter side, mixed up gameplay nicely. \n\nHowever, for me, there was a glaring issue and that was that at some point around the mid-game, I just got a bit bored and that more or less persisted through until the credits rolled. \n\nIt's not that the game's bad after that point and it's rather hard to point to exactly why I felt a bit defeated - I felt that the game was pretty easy and there was little challenge outside of learning a few boss mechanics, the sushi restaurant eventually got to a point where it felt a bit moot I was there, back and forth loading screens going to the farm, etc and forced breaks in dives so \"x thing could happen in y number of days\". \n\nIt just felt a bit jarring, but overall I'm glad I played and finished it - I'll be sure to pick it back up against sometime soon to do the DLC but until then, the fish in the blue hole have a chance to swim without fear of random overweight dudes with harpoons. \n\n7/10",
