    "author_playtime_at_review": 3644,
    "author_deck_playtime_at_review": 0,
    "author_last_played": 1782819347,
    "language": "english",
    "review": "I absolutely ADORE this game. I am a huge fan of Dredge, Stardew, Pixel Art in general, etc... It has so many faucets to play with, from mini-games WITHIN the game itself, farming, business, and of course, the fishing. Collectathons are my jam, and this one goes above and beyond with MarinCa cards, weapons, materials, and all in an ever-changing environment. Even when you understand the base layout, there will always be hidden crevices to explore for certain creatures or items. I usually don't care for the business side of things, but the Sushi Restaurant part of things was very entertaining as well! Everything feels like a challenge that you work hard towards making easier, and even when it becomes easier there is always more to do.\r\n\r\nI think one of the most fantastic parts of the game is the cutscenes. You cannot possibly imagine how hard it is to animate scenes, and to do as much as they did in the game is insane. I rarely skipped repeat Enhancement scenes because the vibe just hits SO much. It adds more depth than you could fathom, and honestly shows how much character and commitment has been put into this game. Although I started with all the DLC, seeing Dredge, Godzilla, and all sorts of things brought in is fantastic. Dredge is my number one fishing game, I want more of it than physically possible, and to have it in Dave the Diver?! I am over the moon ecstatic whenever the fog rolls in. I have yet to go into the Jungle, but I cannot wait to go. Please, if you haven't already, play this game.",
