    "language": "english",
    "review": "Play Dave the Diver.\r\n\r\nSteam has been recommending this game to me for a while, and for months I was like \"Dave? The Diver? nah not for me\". Fishing and running a sushi shop? What is this? Cooking mama? I thought it looked boring. Played Stardew Valley and almost died of boredom, and put this in the same camp.\r\n\r\nEnded up taking a punt in a decent sale to give it a chance on the Steam Deck. Never been more wrong about a game. I don't even know what it is exactly about this game, but I can't put it down. Its simple yet satisfying. I can't put my finger on why, but its nostalgic too even though I can't recall playing a similar game. It just has a retro charm to it. The music is on point, the art style is on point, the character interactions are on point and the game play loop is just fun. Game keeps throwing loads of surprises.",
