    "author_last_played": 1782465645,
    "language": "english",
    "review": "One of the best games I've ever played!!! OwO\r\nSo good that my hands hurt for playing too much lol. I completed all the achievements before reviewing, wew!\r\n\r\nA friend of mine recommended me this game. At first I was worried that it was all grinding, because I prefer games with a story. Turns out I can do both in Dave the Diver. Although, I needed to dive for money, sushi and manage farms, it was surprisingly addictive! Sometimes I didn't notice that my dive lasted for 2 hours lol. \r\n\r\nSpecific things I loved:\r\n- Short, sweet & funny cutscenes / animation (dish enhancement scenes, haha, Bancho gets me everytime)\r\n- Grinding for items/fish doesn't feel overwhelming especially when you're starting out\r\n- The story but is full of heart and humor. The NPCs were fun to interact with\r\n- The soundtracks in this game are a must-listen!\r\n- Some boss fights are actually pretty easy. Some can be challenging but not impossible even for non-gamers.\r\n- Just learned that every staff at level 20 has a custom post on Cooksta. Trying to max out everyone.\r\n- TIP: Use your staff to dispatch for ingredients!!!\r\n\r\nIt's not a perfect game, but it is worth playing after having a bad day. Just dive and have fun!\r\nHappy Anniversary btw!! Thank you, Mintrocket!",
