    "language": "english",
    "review": "~~10/10 \u2013 One of the Most Relaxing and Addictive Games I've Ever Played~~\n\nAfter 47 hours and completing the full story, I can confidently say that Dave the Diver is one of my favorite games I've played in years.\n\nThe gameplay loop is incredibly satisfying: spend your day diving for fish, treasures, and secrets, then come back at night to help run a bustling sushi restaurant. It sounds simple, but the game constantly introduces new mechanics, upgrades, characters, and surprises that keep everything feeling fresh.\n\nWhat really impressed me is how much content is packed into this game. Every time I thought I had seen everything, there was another area to explore, another story beat, or another activity waiting for me. The story was enjoyable, the characters were memorable, and the progression felt rewarding from beginning to end.\n\nEven after finishing the main story, I still find myself wanting to dive back in. There's something genuinely relaxing about exploring the ocean, gathering ingredients, and helping the sushi restaurant thrive. It's become one of those rare games I can play just to unwind and enjoy myself.\n\nI'm also excited for any future DLC because the developers have created a world I genuinely want to keep spending time in.\n\nIf you're looking for a game that's relaxing, charming, funny, packed with content, and incredibly easy to lose hours in, I can't recommend Dave the Diver enough.\n\n  47 hours played. Story completed. Still playing. Still loving it.  \n\n~~10/10 \u2014 Absolutely recommended.~~",
