    "review": "Yeah, really not sure what to say about this. It end up as \"positive\", so let's start with the positive.\nThe aesthetics: The game looks, and feels really nice. Controls are superb (Xbox controller) mostly, music is nice. The story and the characters are lovable. The whole fishing/diving things has a really good feeling alltogether.\n\nThe bad parts:\n-The menu system with the phone is trash. Yeah, we wanted something new... didn't work out.\n-Some of the bosses/challenges were really-really hard for me. Quite a lot of things to manage in an otherwise chill game.\n-There is a LOT of grinding. You want a specific gun, Be prepared to do a TON of fishing for it. And you're gonna need to check guides and all to know where to find stuff.\n-Cutscenes. Too many. Whenever I enter a puzzle area, there is a cutscene about NOTHING. Just let me play for Christ's sake... Also skipping the day... totally useless cutscenes. You have to spend a lot of time waiting for nothing in this game.\n-Genre problems. I get it, indie dev trying out wings and all. But there is a reason why most games aren't like Spore.. and that is a good reason :D\nThis is a fishing game. This is an exploration game. This is a restaurant management game. So far so good.... But it's also a bossfight game... it's also a tamagochi game... for some reason. It's also a guitar hero... for some reason. Sometimes it's Overcooked...\nIt's Mortal Kombat in some areas, and sometimes it's a sidescrolling fighting game.\nOh yeah, it's a farming simulator too...\nAnd of course it's a card game :D Just because....\nOh yeah, and it's a racing game too! And it's a Crocodile/Dino dentist game as well of course.\nThere is a memory game too....\nAnd multiple insances of cups and balls...\nAnd clearly there have to be puzzle-rooms....\n\nAnd many times it's tedious. I am an achievement hunter, which is my problem I get that. And the tamagochi part is not mandatory actually. But it's soooooo boring... and you need to play it a lot to get the achievement.\nI get it, it's fun to experiment, and the game is diverse... but the actual minigames are usually not that good.\n\nDo I recommend the game? Yes, I do!\nBut don't expect a 2 hours indie game. This requires a lot of time to play.\nI am somewhere at around 90 hours, having gathered all the achievements :D\n\nAnd there is an expansion coming in 2 days :D\n\nThis is a big game. And I mean this mostly in a good way, but there is so much useless content in it too...\n\nThe devs love what they are doing, that's for sure :D And it shows every second. This is love-child. And it's fun to experience it. But it has it's faults :)",
