    "language": "english",
    "review": "[h1]Final Score: [b]77/100[/b][/h1]\n\nDave the Diver is the type of game that hooks you early, reels you in slowly, and then keeps revealing more systems long after you think you understand what it is. What starts as a simple game of diving, catching fish, and running a sushi restaurant turns into a surprisingly packed game with upgrades, staff management, farming, side quests, boss fights, collections, events, and more content than expected.\n\nThe gameplay is addictive, satisfying, and easy to return to, though the game can start to feel overloaded as more systems are introduced. The humour is strong point. Its exaggerated characters and playful stereotypes in a way that feels more like older games: less sanitized, less agenda-driven, and more focused on actually being funny for the audience playing it. Duff is a amazing, and the cutscenes give the game a lot of personality.\n\nThe presentation is not perfect. The background music can get repetitive, and some systems feel a bit clunky, but the overall game is far stronger than expected. For the price, Dave the Diver delivers a huge amount of content, a relaxing grind, and a genuinely good time. Recommended.\n\n[h2]Score Breakdown[/h2]\n[b]Gameplay Experience:[/b] 20/25\n[b]Presentation & Immersion:[/b] 14/25\n[b]Design & Technical Aspects:[/b] 20/25\n[b]Final Considerations:[/b] 23/25\n\n[spoiler]Think I got it wrong? Generate your own review at [url=https://playeropinion.com]https://playeropinion.com[/url][/spoiler]",
