    "author_last_played": 1781229581,
    "language": "english",
    "review": "Very great thinking, but the gameplay sometimes end up dissatisfying or even disgusting, \n\nFirst and the most annoying part is the way some interactions work, or how they are designed, it gives me a sticky kind of feeling, like the character is not in my control. Dave reacts very slow to attack command, and the bullet does not hit where the mouse was, because for some unknow reason, the aim arrow is not in line with the top of your mouse icon, WHY IS THAT HAPPENING? I thought its because im not in fullscreen but it was not the reason. Why can't Dave aim up or down? Is it because of some strange realism? The way selection work in this game is also weird,  I end up throwing away items I want, the furniture selection was slow and painful, to sum up,  SO MANY functions can be implemented in a more logical way. I dont want to be strict, But WHY TF does Dave need to have stamina bar when serving? is this function really necessary? Why does the music app exist when you quit the phone music just disappear? It feels like many many things are implemented to show off, its like those kind of unless notes that bad students make when they want to pretend they study hard. \n\nSecond, this game is like a Frankenstein but sewed up by corpse of games, I cant tell which kind of game it wants to be, to some extend its a good thing, but now it a lil too much. I like completing a game, I like grinding, but I hate to be forced to watch cutscenes i dont care, unless dialogues, its like those Anime story telling games. For every in game event your camera is locked, cant move, there will be ?? and !!, feels like those 2d exploration game that have no progression system. And when a game is about fish and sushi? Why are icons of sushi so SMALL?? What is this game trying to be good at?\n\nThat leads to the third, the way information is given is unacceptable, when i need to mind your own things, when you know what will happen and want to skip, the game feeds you with useless info, but mission details is behind pause menu, and phone cant be used underwater, and why does the \"Management\" app exist? it shows the fish in storage, but why do i need that info when im on dry land? the other way around, why do i need to know who is the VIP when im in the water?? just add it as a quest but not a section in the menu, its too much for something that only happens from time to time. Again, the selection related function is a nightmare, to select furniture, you NEED to watch them blink for more and half second before you can do anything else, Excuse me am I BLIND or something? and to select items in your inventory u need to be very careful, because they didnt use any distinctive color or other kind of confirmation, instead they choose to use a small tag at the top right corner, if you like a click through things to quickly see their info, you are going to throw out things you need. I have many ways to make this better, show selected items with a yellow outline, or press a hotkey continuously to enter trash mode, and click on item to dump.\n\nAt the end, these are only my personal feelings, if you are just playing half an hour casually, I think you can bear with it, but if you like fast grinding, if you are familiar enough with these kind of games and want you own fast pace and control, SUFFER, MY FRIEND",
